## Key Design Decisions

| Decision | Rationale |
|---|---|
| **Base font 18px** | Elderly users need larger text; 16px is minimum, 18px is comfortable |
| **Min touch target 48px** | WCAG 2.2 requires minimum 44px; 48px adds comfort margin |
| **Remove `user-scalable=no`** | Blocking zoom is a WCAG Level A violation |
| **CSS classes over inline styles** | Enables hover/focus/active states, media queries, and maintainability |
| **Spell out abbreviations** | "TMA" â†’ "Tempo MÃ©dio" â€” reduces cognitive load for unfamiliar users |
| **Priority: text + icon, not just color** | WCAG requires not relying solely on color for information |
| **Reduced motion support** | Some users have vestibular disorders; animations should be optional |
| **Card-list on mobile** | Data tables with 6+ columns are unusable on 375px screens |

